Class Member

  • java.lang.Object
    • Person
      • Member
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PremiumMember, StudentMember

    public class Member
extends Person
    This class is a subclass of (extends) Person. This class stores the member's height, starting weight, chosenPackage and a hashmap to record the member's progress.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    John Dennehy (Student Number: 20091408)

      • latestAssessment

        public Assessment latestAssessment()
        This method checks if the memberAssessments hashmap is empty. If it is, null is returned. If it is not empty, the assessment returned is the latest one. This is determined by passing the last value in the sortedAssessmentDates() set (the latest date) to the memberAssessments hashmap (using the .get call). This searches for the key value (the last assessment date) and returns the associated object. This is then returned.
        Returns:
        the latest assessment for a member (if available). If no assessments are available, return null.

      • setHeight

        public void setHeight(float height)
        Setter to set the member's height Height entered must be between 1 and 3. Else the user is presented with an error message which informs them that an incorrect value was entered.
        Parameters:
        height - set the member's height to the value passed as a parameter when the method is called.

      • setStartWeight

        public void setStartWeight(float startWeight)

        startWeight - set the member's weight to the value passed as a parameter when the method is called.

      • sortedAssessmentDates

        public java.util.SortedSet<java.lang.String> sortedAssessmentDates()
        This method sorts the assessment dates by passing the keys of the memberAssessments hashmap (assessment dates) to a Treeset. The sorted keys are then available in the orderedAssessments SortedSet.
        Returns:
        the orderedAssessments SortedSet (sorted assessment dates)

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        The toString method returns the member objects in a String format. A call is made to super.toString() to display the member properties inherited from the Person toString() method. The member's height and start weight are appended to this.
